1
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:25,690
- I don't know
where to start, really.

2
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:28,028
Hell, you don't even know me.

3
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:31,779
So I don't expect you to
forgive me for all the things

4
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:32,615
I've done.

5
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:09,772
- Bobby Hawkins.

6
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:12,150
- Birdy.

7
00:03:13,651 --> 00:03:15,276
How about it, man?

8
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:17,780
- Look at you, you
look good, man.

9
00:03:20,783 --> 00:03:22,450
- Last I heard you were
working over at the

10
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:23,659
County Clerk's office

11
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:24,785
- No, man,

12
00:03:24,787 --> 00:03:26,454
I got on over at the plant.

13
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:27,872
Going on six years now.

14
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:28,750
- Shit.

15
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:31,419
- Worked my way
up to Team Leader.

16
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:34,921
- Good for you, man.

17
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:38,843
Come on, you got
what, 9, 10 kids now?

18
00:03:40,762 --> 00:03:43,306
- Three, two girls and a boy.

19
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,682
Best things that
ever happened to me.

20
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:49,310
- I'm happy for you, brother.

21
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:50,853
- Been doing good.

22
00:03:50,855 --> 00:03:52,565
Going out to First Baptist.

23
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:57,276
Alyssa goes out there.

24
00:03:57,278 --> 00:03:58,696
You should come visit some time.

25
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:03,409
You ever talk to her?

26
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:07,830
- Alyssa? She don't
want to talk to me.

27
00:04:09,457 --> 00:04:10,833
- You might be surprised.

28
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:15,838
What's your plan then?

29
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:20,343
- Just... don't go back.

30
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:22,720
- That's a good plan.

31
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:31,854
- Let me ask you
something, Birdy.

32
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:38,945
After all that went down, did
you ever hear from Cofield?

33
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:43,866
- You?

34
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:51,708
I never could figure
it out neither.

35
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:54,669
We was like brothers.

36
00:04:56,754 --> 00:04:59,755
I always figured I'd
hear from him some day.

37
00:04:59,757 --> 00:05:01,718
A letter or something.

38
00:05:04,887 --> 00:05:07,348
- He was the only one
of us that got away.

39
00:05:09,809 --> 00:05:14,439
Sometimes I feel like he's in
some sort of parallel universe

40
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:18,399
sleeping like a baby
on stacks of cash

41
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:21,444
while we're stuck in this one.

42
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:23,489
- Parallel universe, huh?

43
00:05:24,574 --> 00:05:26,034
Man, you was in there too long.

44
00:05:32,623 --> 00:05:34,042
Harry's done good for himself.

45
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:38,419
Owns a bunch of
restaurants, couple of bars,

46
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:40,006
even ran for city commission.

47
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:42,342
- Harry, huh.

48
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:48,429
- Shoot. You, me,
Cofield, Harry.

49
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:51,476
We was something back
in the day, wasn't we?

50
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:53,644
The four horsemen.

51
00:05:55,563 --> 00:05:57,774
- Four stooges, more like it.

52
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:04,364
- Ain't that the truth.

53
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:10,034
It's good to see you, brother.

54
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:10,912
- Hmm.

55
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:18,604
- Battery is low, recharge now.

56
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,564
- Hey buddy.

57
00:08:03,566 --> 00:08:06,901
- Buddy? What is that, a joke?

58
00:08:06,903 --> 00:08:07,778
- Come on, man.

59
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:13,073
- What you think that is? A
toy, something to play with?

60
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:15,451
- I just wanted some company.

61
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:16,577
- Company?

62
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,122
- It gets lonely out here, man.

63
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:20,917
- Would you prefer LaGrange?

64
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:25,129
Look, don't drag my
black ass out here again.

65
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,171
- I'm sorry.

66
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:28,589
- I got things to do.

67
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:29,965
- I know.
- I'm busy.

68
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:30,843
- I know.

69
00:08:32,678 --> 00:08:33,888
- You could have called.

70
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:37,642
- You wouldn't have come.

71
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:43,940
- How's Mrs. Whitaker?

72
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:47,608
- Hell if I know.

73
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:49,610
Hell, man, what did you do?

74
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:51,987
- It's what I didn't do.

75
00:08:51,989 --> 00:08:52,949
I didn't listen.

76
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:56,661
I didn't come home
every night at 6:30.

77
00:08:58,079 --> 00:08:59,497
I didn't leave the
toilet seat down.

78
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,792
I didn't brush my teeth.

79
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:08,047
How's it going looking for work?

80
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,093
- Where am I
supposed to go, huh?

81
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:17,555
Mine's shut down,
factory's full up.

82
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,974
Hell, that's how I got in
this mess in the first place.

83
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:23,185
- Well, you gotta put
some feelers out there.

84
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:25,104
You know that was the deal.

85
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,982
- Well, I got plenty to
keep me busy around here.

86
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:29,110
Look at this place.

87
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:38,244
- Well, I might be able
to help you out with that.

88
00:09:39,787 --> 00:09:41,872
I got a hand, he's
a hard worker.

89
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:52,550
You, you talk to Kelly?

90
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:55,636
- What would I say?

91
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:03,309
- She's still working down
there at the Hideaway.

92
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:05,771
- Hell, that place
ain't burned down yet?

93
00:10:08,065 --> 00:10:09,692
- She still looks the same too.

94
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:15,904
- I'm done with all that mess.

95
00:10:15,906 --> 00:10:17,325
- Yeah, you are.

96
00:10:18,659 --> 00:10:19,869
- Whole 'nother life.

97
00:10:22,371 --> 00:10:24,290
- Here's to a new one.

98
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:26,375
- Let's do it.

99
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,399
- Mr. Hawkins?

100
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:15,357
- Como estas?

101
00:12:15,359 --> 00:12:16,358
- Bien, bien.

102
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,111
- Whitaker send you?

103
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:22,158
He says you need help.

104
00:12:57,109 --> 00:12:58,776
- All right, fellas.

105
00:12:58,778 --> 00:12:59,987
Your wife picking you up?

106
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:03,032
- She takes the
truck on Fridays.

107
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:04,825
- Where to?

108
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,286
- Cleans houses in town.

109
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:12,208
- So you just got
the one vehicle?

110
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:14,084
- We make it work.

111
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:17,963
- Well, I got an
old beater out back.

112
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:20,549
You get her running,
she's yours.

113
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:24,929
Been sitting there 20 years.

114
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:27,223
- You're joking.

115
00:13:29,058 --> 00:13:32,144
- It ain't like I'm doing you
a favor. It's a piece of shit.

116
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:39,068
- Gracias.

117
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:23,881
- What can I get you?

118
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:27,927
You want a drink?

119
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:29,678
- I wanna see her.

120
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:31,639
- For what?

121
00:15:33,057 --> 00:15:34,099
- What do you think?

122
00:15:35,225 --> 00:15:36,975
She's my girl.

123
00:15:36,977 --> 00:15:38,938
- She ain't been
yours for a long time.

124
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,190
- Hell does that mean?

125
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:45,025
I'm her daddy.

126
00:15:45,027 --> 00:15:46,487
- She's got a daddy,
and it ain't you.

127
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,489
- You seeing somebody?

128
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:52,282
- That's none of your business.

129
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:54,203
- Well, Lissy is my business.

130
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:55,913
Where is she?

131
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:58,205
- Hell, Bobby.

132
00:15:58,207 --> 00:15:59,959
That girl ain't lived
with me in years.

133
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:03,504
- Well, if she ain't living
with you, where is she?

134
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:08,256
- Harry took her in.

135
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:09,383
- Harry.

136
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,301
- Shit, Bobby, he's my brother.

137
00:16:11,303 --> 00:16:13,178
I was dead broke.

138
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:14,556
I couldn't afford to raise her.

139
00:16:15,724 --> 00:16:17,349
She's better off.

140
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:19,061
- What the hell
is wrong with you?

141
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:23,063
- You gonna come in here
now like a concerned father

142
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:24,066
and judge me?

143
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:27,236
Get the fuck outta here Bobby.

144
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:29,403
- Give me her number.

145
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:30,447
- I ain't giving you shit.

146
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:34,449
- This guy bothering you?

147
00:16:34,451 --> 00:16:35,953
- He's just leaving.

148
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,498
- Not till I get that number.

149
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,625
- It's time for you
to move on, hoss.

150
00:16:43,627 --> 00:16:45,337
- Take it easy, big boy.

151
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:57,558
- Bobby, here, just go.

152
00:17:11,613 --> 00:17:13,196
- Thought you'd beat me back?

153
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:14,366
- Had some business.

154
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:16,575
- I hope it was worth it.

155
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:18,493
- Look, I ain't going nowhere.

156
00:17:18,495 --> 00:17:23,123
Hell, I'm right here, I'm
just looking for my daughter.

157
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:25,584
- Well, I could'a
helped you with that.

158
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:29,087
- Right, you didn't even tell
me she was living with Harry.

159
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:31,339
- I didn't want you to go
out and do something stupid.

160
00:17:31,341 --> 00:17:33,425
Getting mixed up with
Harry Casper again

161
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:35,385
is something you don't need.

162
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:37,679
You thought he was into
bad shit back in the day,

163
00:17:37,681 --> 00:17:39,765
you should see the
shit he's doing now.

164
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:41,808
- I ain't getting
mixed up with nobody.

165
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:43,727
I'm just trying to see Alyssa.

166
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:48,148
- It's been 10 years, why
you care all of a sudden?

167
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:50,233
- Fuck you, Whitaker.

168
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:54,071
- See, you packing
up the reasons why I
should take you in.

169
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:55,697
- You ain't going to take me in.

170
00:17:55,699 --> 00:17:56,575
- And why not?

171
00:17:58,452 --> 00:18:00,660
- As I recall, you helped me
polish off a bottle of Beam

172
00:18:00,662 --> 00:18:02,329
the other night.

173
00:18:02,331 --> 00:18:03,789
Getting shit-faced
with your parolee...

174
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:06,502
...ain't gonna look too
good to your supervisor.

175
00:18:08,128 --> 00:18:09,296
- You asshole.

176
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:11,381
- Let me go.

177
00:18:14,218 --> 00:18:17,177
- All right. Just this once.

178
00:18:17,179 --> 00:18:20,806
This shit happens again,
blackmail ain't gonna help you.

179
00:18:20,808 --> 00:18:22,518
I can't protect you after this.

180
00:18:23,852 --> 00:18:25,229
- Let me get you a drink.

181
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:27,189
- You asshole.

182
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:05,144
- Look at you.

183
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:07,479
Ain't changed a lick.

184
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:11,567
Maybe a little uglier.

185
00:19:12,609 --> 00:19:15,154
Ain't you going to invite me in?

186
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:21,451
- Hoo-wee, it's
been a long time.

187
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:25,164
So how long you been out and
you ain't come to see me?

188
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:27,581
- Been busy.

189
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:30,127
- Hmm, that's what I hear.

190
00:19:31,461 --> 00:19:33,587
Kelly says you was
down at the Hideaway,

191
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:34,756
asking about Lissy.

192
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:39,761
- How's she doing?

193
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:42,681
- Just let me worry about her.

194
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:53,400
Pere... Perelandra?

195
00:19:57,321 --> 00:19:58,780
You getting all egghead on me?

196
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:12,667
Hey, you remember the
time that we stacked

197
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:15,420
all those beer cans
up on your daddy's TV

198
00:20:15,422 --> 00:20:18,634
and then we took
turns swinging at it?

199
00:20:19,718 --> 00:20:22,387
- Yeah, except you missed.

200
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:26,266
Busted the shit outta
your daddy's Magnavox.

201
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:29,978
- He beat the tar outta me.

202
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:35,901
How can I help you, Harry?

203
00:20:37,444 --> 00:20:39,279
- Oh, I'm glad
you asked me that.

204
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,244
You got something
that belongs to me.

205
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:52,999
- Money's long gone.
Cofield took every penny.

206
00:20:53,001 --> 00:20:53,877
- Oh did he now?

207
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:56,672
- I was there.

208
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:00,298
I watched him cross
over into Jellico.

209
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,802
That's the last I seen him.

210
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:06,680
- Well, now I know that's
what you told the press

211
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:08,306
and the cops.

212
00:21:08,308 --> 00:21:12,312
But, see, I never
believed that story.

213
00:21:13,855 --> 00:21:17,816
Because, see, you was the
greediest one of the whole bunch

214
00:21:17,818 --> 00:21:20,860
and there ain't no way in
hell you would've let Cofield

215
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:22,946
light out with all that cash.

216
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:24,366
- I was scared, man.

217
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:28,743
I figured that if
he had the money,

218
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:30,662
the cops would go
after him and not me.

219
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:33,707
I come home and there's a
shit load of cherry-toppers

220
00:21:33,709 --> 00:21:35,458
in my driveway.

221
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:36,712
- So he sold you out, huh?

222
00:21:37,921 --> 00:21:38,797
- Maybe.

223
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:45,345
- That is about 10 pounds of
horse shit in a 5 pound bag.

224
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:49,431
I think you know
exactly what happened.

225
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:51,850
And it had nothing
to do with Cofield

226
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:55,520
riding off into
the sunset, did it?

227
00:21:55,522 --> 00:21:58,606
- That was 13 years ago.

228
00:21:58,608 --> 00:22:00,859
That shit's over and done with.

229
00:22:00,861 --> 00:22:04,364
- You're a changed
man. You and Birdy.

230
00:22:05,574 --> 00:22:07,073
Done found Jesus.

231
00:22:07,075 --> 00:22:09,953
You done got washed in
the blood of the Lamb.

232
00:22:11,705 --> 00:22:12,664
See, the problem is,

233
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:16,418
the blood doesn't wash
away what you owe.

234
00:22:18,086 --> 00:22:20,420
- I ain't in debt to you.

235
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:21,755
- Au contraire.

236
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:24,549
See, we made a pact.

237
00:22:24,551 --> 00:22:26,843
We was all gonna split
that money up four ways.

238
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:31,514
Now, in my mind, when a
man makes pact, it stands

239
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:36,311
and it don't matter no
nevermind how many years pass.

240
00:22:36,313 --> 00:22:38,438
- From what I hear, you
own half the county.

241
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,983
What do you need more money for?

242
00:22:41,818 --> 00:22:43,945
Look, I wish I could
help you, Harry.

243
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:56,541
- I'm gonna get my money.

244
00:22:57,959 --> 00:23:00,796
Maybe not today.
Maybe not tomorrow.

245
00:23:03,924 --> 00:23:05,509
But I'm gonna get what's mine.

246
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:14,810
Whoa, you should have
seen your face right then.

247
00:23:19,439 --> 00:23:20,855
- I'd like to see Alyssa.

248
00:23:20,857 --> 00:23:22,651
- Oh, I bet you would.

249
00:23:24,361 --> 00:23:27,114
- Look, I appreciate you
helping her out and everything.

250
00:23:30,784 --> 00:23:31,827
- Helping her out?

251
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:39,668
You make it, I don't know,
sound like I just, I don't know,

252
00:23:41,044 --> 00:23:43,505
bought her some school
books or shit like that.

253
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:48,552
I raised that girl.

254
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:54,516
- And I appreciate all
you done. All the same...

255
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:58,562
- You have a good
day, Bobby boy.

256
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:12,617
- How's it coming?

257
00:24:14,035 --> 00:24:17,205
- Levantando a los muertos.

258
00:24:18,832 --> 00:24:21,209
My daughter, she
ain't picking up.

259
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:24,878
- She probably don't
know it's you calling.

260
