00:42:36,512 --> 00:42:40,641
This guy, Ransom, he fights an
evil force to restore Earth.

525
00:42:44,770 --> 00:42:49,525
Let me see... listen to this.

526
00:42:51,277 --> 00:42:54,528
"The smells in the
forest were beyond all

527
00:42:54,530 --> 00:42:56,907
that he had ever conceived.

528
00:42:58,242 --> 00:42:59,992
To say that they
made him feel hungry

529
00:42:59,994 --> 00:43:01,996
and thirsty would be misleading.

530
00:43:03,581 --> 00:43:06,166
They created a new kind
of hunger and thirst,

531
00:43:07,793 --> 00:43:10,252
a longing that seemed to
flow over from the body

532
00:43:10,254 --> 00:43:11,672
into the soul..."

533
00:43:12,965 --> 00:43:13,841
What's the matter?

534
00:43:15,175 --> 00:43:16,176
- I gotta go.

535
00:43:17,928 --> 00:43:21,348
- I'd like to see you
again. I mean, if you want.

536
00:43:23,726 --> 00:43:26,228
Well, at least take
the book, it's good.

537
00:43:59,970 --> 00:44:00,846
- Hell is this?

538
00:44:02,765 --> 00:44:04,056
- A book.

539
00:44:04,058 --> 00:44:05,267
- Oh, no shit.

540
00:44:06,602 --> 00:44:07,394
Where'd you get it?

541
00:44:10,731 --> 00:44:12,066
Went and seen him, didn't you?

542
00:44:13,609 --> 00:44:15,944
Now what did I tell
you about that?

543
00:44:17,404 --> 00:44:20,614
- I just --
- Oh I just, I just what?

544
00:44:20,616 --> 00:44:22,366
Let me ask you something.

545
00:44:22,368 --> 00:44:24,284
Who do you think it was that
kept a roof over your head,

546
00:44:24,286 --> 00:44:25,913
ever since you was yay high?

547
00:44:27,081 --> 00:44:30,248
See, I know what
is best for you.

548
00:44:30,250 --> 00:44:32,751
And he's got nothing
to say in the matter.

549
00:44:32,753 --> 00:44:35,879
Now what part of that
does your little pea brain

550
00:44:35,881 --> 00:44:37,714
not understand?

551
00:44:37,716 --> 00:44:39,633
- I just wanted to meet him.

552
00:44:39,635 --> 00:44:40,302
- What for?

553
00:44:42,638 --> 00:44:43,929
- I got a right.

554
00:44:43,931 --> 00:44:45,639
- You what?

555
00:44:45,641 --> 00:44:48,225
- I got a right to
see him if I want.

556
00:44:48,227 --> 00:44:49,851
- Oh, you got a right...

557
00:44:49,853 --> 00:44:52,729
You got a right to do
exactly what I say.

558
00:44:52,731 --> 00:44:54,066
- Screw you, Harry.

559
00:44:57,152 --> 00:45:02,072
- Now listen, everything
you got, everything you are

560
00:45:02,074 --> 00:45:06,912
is because of me, and
don't ever forget it.

561
00:45:28,183 --> 00:45:29,727
- How you doing, Mr. Hawkins?

562
00:45:31,061 --> 00:45:32,811
- I'm doing.

563
00:45:32,813 --> 00:45:34,398
- Your daughter around?

564
00:45:35,941 --> 00:45:37,357
- Why?

565
00:45:37,359 --> 00:45:39,778
- Apparently, she
ran off last night.

566
00:45:41,321 --> 00:45:43,198
- Well, she hadn't
come around here.

567
00:45:44,283 --> 00:45:45,866
You check with her mother?

568
00:45:45,868 --> 00:45:47,951
- Yeah, she ain't
been by there neither.

569
00:45:47,953 --> 00:45:49,121
But I wouldn't worry.

570
00:45:50,414 --> 00:45:51,747
- You wouldn't, huh?

571
00:45:51,749 --> 00:45:53,290
- No, you know how kids are.

572
00:45:53,292 --> 00:45:54,833
She probably got pissed at Harry

573
00:45:54,835 --> 00:45:56,879
and ran off to a
friend's for a few days.

574
00:45:58,338 --> 00:46:00,382
But she comes by, you
let me know, okay?

575
00:46:07,806 --> 00:46:08,474
- Shit.

576
00:46:13,228 --> 00:46:15,353
- Give it a couple
days, she'll show up.

577
00:46:15,355 --> 00:46:18,023
- Hell, it's my fault,
I let Harry raise her.

578
00:46:18,025 --> 00:46:19,983
I got no right to be concerned.

579
00:46:19,985 --> 00:46:21,945
- Sure you do, she's your kid.

580
00:46:24,782 --> 00:46:25,866
I need your help, Birdy.

581
00:46:26,909 --> 00:46:28,867
You're right.

582
00:46:28,869 --> 00:46:31,745
Alyssa is my blood, I don't
care if I'm stuck out here.

583
00:46:31,747 --> 00:46:33,997
I ain't gonna let him hurt her.

584
00:46:33,999 --> 00:46:35,916
- What do you need me to do?

585
00:46:35,918 --> 00:46:38,001
- I need you to go to Harry

586
00:46:38,003 --> 00:46:39,753
and tell him he don't
run things no more.

587
00:46:39,755 --> 00:46:41,963
- Bobby, I don't want to
get caught up in no war.

588
00:46:41,965 --> 00:46:43,842
- Just give him the message.

589
00:46:45,219 --> 00:46:46,261
You owe me that.

590
00:47:55,998 --> 00:47:57,541
- Have a seat, Birdy.

591
00:48:05,007 --> 00:48:08,302
So, you come here
to save my soul?

592
00:48:09,386 --> 00:48:10,929
- Ain't nothing like that.

593
00:48:12,514 --> 00:48:14,600
- That's good cause you'd
be wasting your time.

594
00:48:16,393 --> 00:48:18,353
But now you gotta tell me
why you're here wasting mine.

595
00:48:19,980 --> 00:48:21,273
- Bobby Hawkins sent me.

596
00:48:23,275 --> 00:48:24,610
- You're Bobby's pigeon now.

597
00:48:26,153 --> 00:48:27,487
- He'd have come
himself if he could.

598
00:48:31,158 --> 00:48:34,411
- You got balls, Birdy,
I'll tell you that, you do.

599
00:48:35,996 --> 00:48:39,080
But, you know, coming
here on Bobby's behalf,

600
00:48:39,082 --> 00:48:44,046
I can't tell whether that's
really brave or really stupid.

601
00:48:47,507 --> 00:48:50,967
- Bobby's just worried about
his little girl is all.

602
00:48:50,969 --> 00:48:52,262
- Sounds like an accusation.

603
00:48:53,347 --> 00:48:54,389
- Nothing like that.

604
00:48:57,184 --> 00:49:00,020
- Well then, tell me
what it is like, Birdy.

605
00:49:02,356 --> 00:49:05,567
- Bobby just don't think
she's safe here is all.

606
00:49:07,653 --> 00:49:10,362
- Well, that's none
of Bobby's business.

607
00:49:10,364 --> 00:49:12,280
Sure as hell ain't
none of yours.

608
00:49:12,282 --> 00:49:14,908
- Shoot, Harry.

609
00:49:14,910 --> 00:49:18,205
Back in the day, he took
the fall for all of us.

610
00:49:19,247 --> 00:49:21,164
If it hadn't been for Bobby,

611
00:49:21,166 --> 00:49:23,293
you and me both would've done
a lot more time than we did.

612
00:49:24,378 --> 00:49:26,088
We all robbed that place.

613
00:49:27,464 --> 00:49:30,006
But you and me did
three piddly years.

614
00:49:30,008 --> 00:49:32,008
Knowing that he was in
there that whole time,

615
00:49:32,010 --> 00:49:34,678
I don't know about you,
but that killed me.

616
00:49:34,680 --> 00:49:37,557
- So, what, you think
we owe him something?

617
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:40,227
Let me ask you something, Birdy.

618
00:49:41,979 --> 00:49:44,231
You say Bobby's so concerned
about his little girl.

619
00:49:48,151 --> 00:49:52,364
Just exactly what does
he intend to do about it?

620
00:49:54,700 --> 00:49:56,952
- He just says to tell you

621
00:49:58,578 --> 00:50:01,623
that he ain't afraid to
tussle if it comes to that.

622
00:50:13,301 --> 00:50:15,301
Listen, I ain't trying
to stir nothing up.

623
00:50:15,303 --> 00:50:16,513
It's what he said.

624
00:50:18,765 --> 00:50:22,684
- Come in my house uninvited.
Call me an unfit guardian.

625
00:50:22,686 --> 00:50:24,146
Pass along a threat.

626
00:50:25,564 --> 00:50:27,272
And you ain't trying
to stir nothing up?

627
00:50:27,274 --> 00:50:29,649
- You ain't my enemy, Harry.

628
00:50:29,651 --> 00:50:31,484
- Birdy, Birdy...

629
00:50:31,486 --> 00:50:33,611
I really thought you were
smarter than this, I really did.

630
00:50:33,613 --> 00:50:35,780
I mean, you went and
got yourself on the
straight and narrow

631
00:50:35,782 --> 00:50:39,534
but you haven't got the sense

632
00:50:39,536 --> 00:50:43,371
God gave a three-legged
coon dog who's lost his nose

633
00:50:43,373 --> 00:50:45,792
and ought to be put down.

634
00:50:47,294 --> 00:50:48,587
- Please don't
shoot the messenger.

635
00:50:50,672 --> 00:50:53,717
- Don't worry, Birdy...
I ain't gonna shoot you.

636
00:51:28,794 --> 00:51:31,546
- To think we used
to be friends.

637
00:51:38,178 --> 00:51:38,845
- Stooges.

638
00:51:40,347 --> 00:51:41,681
- What?
- Stooges.

639
00:51:46,311 --> 00:51:50,315
- Boys, show him what we
do to uninvited guests.

640
00:52:48,748 --> 00:52:51,916
- Morning. What are
you girls doing?

641
00:52:51,918 --> 00:52:52,878
- Just walking.

642
00:52:54,129 --> 00:52:55,587
- Why don't you get in the car?

643
00:52:55,589 --> 00:52:56,921
- We ain't done nothing.

644
00:52:56,923 --> 00:52:58,798
- Oh, you're not in trouble.

645
00:52:58,800 --> 00:53:00,886
I promise. There's some
people worried about you.

646
00:53:02,220 --> 00:53:02,888
Come on.

647
00:53:35,587 --> 00:53:36,588
Mr. Hawkins.

648
00:53:37,505 --> 00:53:38,924
- What's going on?

649
00:53:40,717 --> 00:53:43,259
- We, uh... we pulled
Lawrence Birdwhistle's car

650
00:53:43,261 --> 00:53:45,305
out of Benson
Creek this morning.

651
00:53:46,973 --> 00:53:47,807
- Where is he?

652
00:53:49,392 --> 00:53:51,603
- He was inside, he
was beat to death.

653
00:53:56,858 --> 00:53:59,525
His wife said y'all
spoke the other day.

654
00:53:59,527 --> 00:54:00,612
What'd you talk about?

655
00:54:02,280 --> 00:54:03,821
- You think I had
something to do with it?

656
00:54:03,823 --> 00:54:05,573
- No one is saying that.

657
00:54:05,575 --> 00:54:07,200
- Birdy was my friend.

658
00:54:07,202 --> 00:54:08,493
If you want to know
what happened to him,

659
00:54:08,495 --> 00:54:09,786
why don't you ask Harry Casper?

660
00:54:09,788 --> 00:54:11,663
- I intend to.

661
00:54:11,665 --> 00:54:14,958
- And why aren't y'all out
there looking for my daughter?

662
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:17,585
- Alyssa's home, I picked
her up this morning.

663
00:54:17,587 --> 00:54:19,504
She's over at Harry's now.

664
00:54:19,506 --> 00:54:21,883
- Hell, then she's in more
trouble than she ever was.

665
00:54:23,468 --> 00:54:25,426
- Harry Casper is
her legal guardian,

666
00:54:25,428 --> 00:54:27,387
there is nothing we
can do about that.

667
00:54:27,389 --> 00:54:30,767
- There's nothing you can
do about anything, is there?

668
00:54:34,354 --> 00:54:35,770
What good are them badges

669
00:54:35,772 --> 00:54:37,563
if y'all are all
working for Harry?

670
00:54:37,565 --> 00:54:39,023
- Well, what good is this badge

671
00:54:39,025 --> 00:54:40,358
if you won't tell
me what you know

672
00:54:40,360 --> 00:54:41,486
that'll help me bring him in?

673
00:54:43,947 --> 00:54:46,741
- I told you... I
ain't hiding nothing.

674
00:55:22,694 --> 00:55:24,446
- Sorry to hear
about your friend.

675
00:55:27,449 --> 00:55:29,284
- Who knows what
he's gonna do next?

676
00:55:30,535 --> 00:55:32,287
I gotta get Alyssa out of there.

677
00:55:33,371 --> 00:55:34,829
- And how you gonna do that?

678
00:55:34,831 --> 00:55:36,748
The second you leave,
every black and white

679
00:55:36,750 --> 00:55:38,583
in the county is
gonna be on your ass.

680
00:55:38,585 --> 00:55:40,460
What good you gonna
do her back in prison?

681
00:55:40,462 --> 00:55:41,755
- I gotta do something.

682
00:55:43,298 --> 00:55:44,672
- Bobby, let the cops
take care of this.

683
00:55:44,674 --> 00:55:46,299
- The cops.

684
00:55:46,301 --> 00:55:47,633
- They're your best
friends right now.

685
00:55:47,635 --> 00:55:49,052
- Some friends.
- Let them do their job.

686
00:55:49,054 --> 00:55:52,930
- They did their job,
and Birdy's dead.

687
00:55:52,932 --> 00:55:55,600
I ain't gonna sit around
and wait for the same thing

688
00:55:55,602 --> 00:55:56,978
to happen to Alyssa.

689
00:55:58,563 --> 00:55:59,773
- You ain't got
a lot of options.

690
00:56:02,567 --> 00:56:04,069
- I thought you were on my side.

691
00:56:05,820 --> 00:56:07,322
- I ain't on nobody's side.

692
00:56:08,948 --> 00:56:11,910
My job is to keep you
out of prison, that's it.

693
00:56:13,495 --> 00:56:15,622
These days, you ain't
making that very easy.

694
00:56:43,358 --> 00:56:44,649
- Alyssa?

695
00:56:44,651 --> 00:56:46,778
It's your... Bobby Hawkins.

696
00:56:47,987 --> 00:56:50,907
Listen, can you come out here?

697
00:56:51,991 --> 00:56:53,410
I'd like to talk to you.

698
00:56:55,662 --> 00:56:56,496
Yeah.

699
00:57:37,579 --> 00:57:38,538
- What do you want?

700
00:57:39,831 --> 00:57:41,708
- Listen, I know Harry's
got a hold on you.

701
00:57:42,625 --> 00:57:44,041
Believe it or not,

702
00:57:44,043 --> 00:57:45,960
he had the same hold
on me back in the day.

703
00:57:45,962 --> 00:57:47,670
- Nobody's got no hold on me.

704
00:57:47,672 --> 00:57:49,088
- Then get out of there.

705
00:57:49,090 --> 00:57:50,715
- And go where?

706
00:57:50,717 --> 00:57:53,718
- Here. Come stay with
me. You'll be safe.

707
00:57:53,720 --> 00:57:55,054
- I don't even know you.

708
00:57:57,974 --> 00:57:59,434
- For the longest time,

709
00:58:01,019 --> 00:58:03,102
I sat up there in
that rock thinking

710
00:58:03,104 --> 00:58:08,109
I wasn't worthy or something
to be your daddy, you know?

711
00:58:09,652 --> 00:58:11,863
Like you were better
off without me.

712
00:58:13,698 --> 00:58:16,159
Figured you felt the same,
so I stopped writing.

713
00:58:18,870 --> 00:58:19,996
- You never wrote me.

714
00:58:22,081 --> 00:58:24,083
- I wrote you two
years straight.

715
00:58:25,460 --> 00:58:26,920
- I never got no letters.

716
00:58:30,590 --> 00:58:32,675
- You may want to ask
your mom about that.

717
00:58:34,594 --> 00:58:37,011
All I'm asking is that
you give me a chance.

718
00:58:37,013 --> 00:58:38,515
- You had your chance.

719
00:58:40,141 --> 00:58:42,767
Harry's right, he's the only
one ever gave a shit about me.

720
00:58:42,769 --> 00:58:44,936
- Harry only cares about Harry.

721
00:58:44,938 --> 00:58:47,104
- Cares more than you ever did.

722
00:58:47,106 --> 00:58:49,815
Ever since you come around,
everything's gone to shit.

723
00:58:49,817 --> 00:58:51,484
And I don't want no part of it.

724
00:58:51,486 --> 00:58:52,985
- What do you want?

725
00:58:52,987 --> 00:58:55,196
- I just want things
to go back to normal.

726
00:58:55,198 --> 00:58:58,157
- Back to him
smacking you around?

727
00:58:58,159 --> 00:59:00,117
- You don't get it, do you?

728
00:59:00,119 --> 00:59:02,745
I'm glad you got that
thing on your ankle.

729
00:59:02,747 --> 00:59:04,914
I don't ever wanna
see you again.

730
00:59:04,916 --> 00:59:06,874
I don't want you to call me.

731
00:59:06,876 --> 00:59:09,837
You was never my dad and
you're never gonna be.

732
01:00:53,608 --> 01:00:55,902
- What's on your mind, sugar?

733
01:00:58,404 --> 01:01:00,696
- I know you're
working for Harry.

734
01:01:00,698 --> 01:01:02,408
They got you keeping
an eye on me.

735
01:01:05,244 --> 01:01:06,245
It's all right.

736
01:01:08,956 --> 01:01:11,332
You're just doing
what you gotta do.

737
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:13,042
- Bobby...

738
01:01:13,044 --> 01:01:14,671
- You know what's fucked up?

739
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:18,383
I had a plan.

740
01:01:21,719 --> 01:01:26,222
Soon as I got out, I was
gonna get what was mine

741
01:01:26,224 --> 01:01:28,976
and get the hell outta
here and never look back.

742
01:01:34,065 --> 01:01:38,069
Then I saw Alyssa and
all this shit went down.

743
01:01:44,701 --> 01:01:49,706
I thought I never wanted to
see her again, but I was wrong.

744
01:01:50,456 --> 01:01:51,124
I just didn't know it.

745
01:01:58,464 --> 01:01:59,841
You got kids?

746
01:02:03,010 --> 01:02:06,303
- Two. Boy and a girl.

747
01:02:06,305 --> 01:02:07,223
- So you know.

748
01:02:08,850 --> 01:02:11,477
- Everything I do is for them.

749
01:02:13,312 --> 01:02:16,856
- They ever have bad dreams?

750
01:02:16,858 --> 01:02:18,985
- About every other night.

751
01:02:21,112 --> 01:02:23,156
- I have this dream sometimes.

752
01:02:27,076 --> 01:02:29,078
I'm underground, buried

753
01:02:33,916 --> 01:02:36,002
but I'm still alive.

754
01:02:40,339 --> 01:02:44,759
And these snakes
break through the dirt

755
01:02:44,761 --> 01:02:48,222
and they wrap around me.

756
01:02:54,228 --> 01:02:59,190
The crazy thing is, I
don't try to fight it.

757
01:02:59,192 --> 01:03:00,193
- What do you mean?

758
01:03:03,112 --> 01:03:04,322
- I deserve it.

759
01:03:07,742 --> 01:03:09,952
I belong there with the snakes.

760
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:14,749
- You done your time.

761
01:03:16,292 --> 01:03:18,044
What are you still paying for?

762
01:03:25,218 --> 01:03:26,928
- What are you still doing here?

763
01:03:28,304 --> 01:03:31,055
- Oh, what you,
you want me to go?

764
01:03:31,057 --> 01:03:33,392
- I mean here in Devil's Hollow.

765
01:03:37,230 --> 01:03:40,356
If you could get outta
here, go anywhere,

766
01:03:40,358 --> 01:03:41,275
what would you do?

767
01:03:42,527 --> 01:03:44,070
- Pack up my kids.

768
01:03:45,822 --> 01:03:47,406
Go down to Clearwater.

769
01:03:55,331 --> 01:03:56,207
- Do it.

770
01:03:57,875 --> 01:03:59,500
- I can't.

771
01:03:59,502 --> 01:04:01,921
- Take your kids,
and get outta here.

772
01:04:15,601 --> 01:04:18,062
- You just going to
up and skedaddle, huh?

773
01:04:19,272 --> 01:04:21,188
- I'm tired of all this.

774
01:04:21,190 --> 01:04:26,112
- Well, at least have one
last drink with your boy.

775
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:28,906
- I really gotta go.
- Sit.

